-- Tishman, Lehman near deal for Archstone-Smith: WSJ
-- 
-- Mon May 28, 2007 7:46pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/05/28/businesspro-archstonesmith-deal-dc-idUSN2827757220070528

 

 PHILADELPHIA  (Reuters) - Tishman Speyer Properties and 
Lehman Brothers Holdings Inc. LEH.N are close to a deal to 
acquire real estate investment trust Archstone-Smith Trust 
( ASN.N ), according to the online edition of The Wall Street 
Journal. 

  The total value of the deal could top $20 billion, 
including debt, the report said.  Shares of Archstone rose about 8 percent on Friday after 
reports that Tishman and Archstone were in discussions about a 
transaction, the report said. The U.S. financial markets were 
closed on Monday for the Memorial Day holiday.  Lehman, Tishman and Archstone-Smith could not be 
immediately reached for comment.